															>Click here to watch Infographic Video of the
															above scheme</a
														>
													</figcaption>
												</figure>
												<div class="tbl mt-4">
													<table class="table table-striped">
														<thead>
															<tr>
																<th scope="col">Administrator</th>
																<th scope="col">Functions</th>
															</tr>
														</thead>
														<tbody>
															<tr>
																<th>School Director</th>
																<td>
																	Reviewing various reports on educational,
																	administrative, and financial performance.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>School Principal</th>
																<td>
																	Supervising educational process, following up
																	study plan, and reviewing various reports.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>System Administrator</th>
																<td>
																	Managing the system settings, and users and
																	their privileges, and doing daily backups.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>School Registrar</th>
																<td>
																	Receiving new students, managing student data
																	and documents, and granting online
																	registration.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Cashier</th>
																<td>
																	Issuing payment documents, paying and
																	recording expenses, and following up due
																	payments.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Accounting Management</th>
																<td>
																	Performing all school financial tasks
																	including configuring settings, making
																	transactions, and generating reports.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Secretary</th>
																<td>
																	Editing school pages and news bulletin on the
																	website, and managing related media and
																	surveys.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Transport Officer</th>
																<td>
																	Designing buses’ routes, following up
																	students’ subscriptions, and managing drivers’
																	wages and expenses.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Education Officer</th>
																<td>
																	Preparing timetable for different grades and
																	classes, assigning teachers and following up
																	their performance, and approving syllabus.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Grade Supervisors</th>
																<td>
																	Monitoring students' attendance, contacting
																	parents, and following up teachers
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Teachers</th>
																<td>
																	Taking students' attendance, implementing
																	study plan, providing syllabus summary,
																	preparing traditional and online exams, and
																	recording grades.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Students</th>
																<td>
																	Submitting homework, taking online exams, and
																	requesting absence permission.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Parents</th>
																<td>
																	Communicating with school officials, following
																	up attendance and grades, and paying fees
																	online.
																</td>
															</tr>
															<tr>
																<th>Examination Officer</th>
																<td>
																	Managing, following up, and documenting exams’
																	procedures in details.
																</td>
															</tr>
														</tbody>
